==="You will bear the blazing sun, until... dawn breaks..."{{subst:void|<!--104050432-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=trailblaze|location=The 2003432nd Eternal Recurrence: Styxia|update|Do you still remember her, Khaslana, the one who won't reach the dawn?<br />Castorice, with every sigh flowing from her fingertips and her hands blocking all words of comfort, she held each death close to her heart and swallowed every cry of grief in her palms.<br />Tell me, if Kephale never forgets, how many pairs of wings have you shattered for her? How many blossoms have you snuffed out? How many butterflies have you cast into the ashes?<br />The moonlight's fragrance once streamed like the River of Souls. How did you turn it into golden poison and make it libations for your banquet of futile deliverance?<br />And yet it is you, so-called Deliverer in sheep's clothing, who ought to be the sacrifice upon the altar to the gods!<br />Ugly beast &mdash; your seemingly pious gaze cannot hide the seething venom beneath. And that spear-like horn of yours was born to slay your kin.<br />So feast upon bones and call it grace. The sweetness will surely convince you: "I never truly knew anything about the blade of slaughter."}}
{{Dialogue Start}}
:{{tx}}
{{Dialogue End}}

===Bid farewell to The Hero Within{{subst:void|<!--104050438-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=trailblaze|location=The Homeland Within|update|Do you still remember, Khaslana, the one who won't reach the dawn?<br />In that drunken dream, the mountains loomed high and steep &mdash; and there, you saw yourself.<br />Believe me, O future witness &mdash; he stood atop that peak, and the people sang with him in ecstasy.<br />The broken Chrysos Heirs, the twisted demigods &mdash; they sang, they spun, they stamped their feet upon the ground with him.<br />Hail! Terror struck his heart: Prophecy burned in every soul, wild with rapture and madness.<br />Hail! Spare them, Khaslana, spare them &mdash; your peerless flame sends chills down every spine!<br />Let them sing of the tireless heroes, sing of the Era Nova, sing of that land where wine and honey flow in torrents.<br />Let them sing how he wove new glory among the stars, and how the Eternal City crashed to dust.<br />How Okhemans, Castrum Kremnos, and every lineage they knew were destroyed.<br />As for Khaslana &mdash; He is still within the drunken dreams, upon the sheer and jagged peak!<br />There he lights flame with blood, and blood with flame, like a sun whose blaze banished all evil from its path.<br />The mountains rise cruel and steep. Yet still he dances there alone, wild and unceasing in his joy.<br />Yet all proves futile &mdash; the flames know no weariness, and dawn is beyond reach.<br />All proves futile &mdash; the flames know no weariness, and dawn is beyond reach.}}
{{Dialogue Start}}
